Students are expected to learn fundamental concepts related to satellite development and design. Students are encouraged to explore the recent advancements and trends in satellite technologies, such as CubeSats and virtual satellite constellations for various purposes. After taking this course, students should be able to:

1. Understand the major hardware components of satellites and procedures of satellite design and launching;
2. Understand the fundamental concepts of remote sensing and imagery processing;
3. Describe the applications of Earth observation satellites;
4. Describe the applications of CubeSats and satellite constellations.

